 "modules": [
  {
   "title": "Module 1 · Matrix Operations",
   "html": "<p>Add/subtract matrices of the same order entrywise. Multiply matrices $A_{m\\times n}$ and $B_{n\\times p}$ so that the number of columns of $A$ equals rows of $B$; the entry $(i,j)$ of $AB$ is the dot product of row $i$ of $A$ with column $j$ of $B$.</p>",
   "examples": [
    {
     "q": "If $A=\\begin{pmatrix}1&2\\\\3&4\\end{pmatrix}$ and $B=\\begin{pmatrix}2&0\\\\1&3\\end{pmatrix}$, find $AB$.",
     "a": "$AB=\\begin{pmatrix}1\\cdot2+2\\cdot1 & 1\\cdot0+2\\cdot3\\\\3\\cdot2+4\\cdot1 & 3\\cdot0+4\\cdot3\\end{pmatrix}=\\begin{pmatrix}4&6\\\\10&12\\end{pmatrix}$."
    }
   ]
  },
  {
   "title": "Module 2 · Determinant & Inverse of a 2×2",
   "html": "<p>For $A=\\begin{pmatrix}a&b\\\\c&d\\end{pmatrix}$:</p>$$\\det A = ad - bc,\\qquad A^{-1} = \\dfrac{1}{ad-bc}\\begin{pmatrix}d&-b\\\\-c&a\\end{pmatrix}$$<p>An inverse exists iff $\\det A \\ne 0$.</p>",
   "examples": [
    {
     "q": "Find the determinant of $\\begin{pmatrix}3&5\\\\2&4\\end{pmatrix}$.",
     "a": "$\\det = 3\\cdot 4 - 5\\cdot 2 = 12 - 10 = 2$."
    }
   ]
  },
  {
   "title": "Module 3 · Cramer's Rule",
   "html": "<p>For $ax+by=e$, $cx+dy=f$ with $D=ad-bc\\ne 0$:</p>$$x=\\dfrac{ed-bf}{D},\\qquad y=\\dfrac{af-ec}{D}$$",
   "examples": [
    {
     "q": "Solve $2x+3y=8$, $x-y=1$ using Cramer's rule.",
     "a": "$D=2(-1)-3(1)=-5$. $x=(8(-1)-3(1))/-5=(-11)/-5=11/5$. $y=(2(1)-8(1))/-5=(-6)/-5=6/5$. (Or directly: $x=2,y=1$? Check: substitution gives $D=-5, x=(-11)/-5=2.2$; consistent with $2(2.2)+3(1.2)=4.4+3.6=8$ ✓.)"
    }
   ]
  }
 ],
